++ is the incriment command
-- is the decriment command
= is just defines and assigns values
+= adds value to variable
-= decreases value to variable
*= multiples variable by value
/= divides variable by value
%= performs modulo on variable

== checks if values are equal
!= checks if not equal
> is a comparison operator
< is a comparison operator 

&& Logical and returns true if both true
|| Logical or returns true if either true
! Logical not reverses result returns false if the result is true

s.length() Counts how many chars are in String (including spaces)
s.toUpperCase() CONVERTS ALL TO UPPER CASE
s.toLowerCase() converts all to lower case
s.indexOf("o") Finds location of char

JAVA CONVERTS STRINGS TO AN INTEGER AUTOMATICALLY!



\' is the escape character. It returns:
'

\\ returns:
\

ESSENTAILLY, IT PREVENTS THE CHARACTER FROM BEING RECOGNIZED AS A RESERVED CHAR.

